The paper deals with security analyses of networked systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of a stochastic model to quantify security, which involves the use of probability and statistics, making it relevant to the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and statistical computing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of tuning system configurations and parameters to improve security, which is relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of simulation studies to confirm analytic results, which is relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as simulation studies often involve the use of machine learning and other AI techniques.
